style="text-align: justify; font-size: 19px;">In this lab I will be interacting with Pfsense to Pfsense IPsec tunnel mode VPN. The tunnels are setup in Virtual Tunnel Interface (VTI) mode.</p><p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 19px;">All the routers are running OSPF for routing over the VTI. div.p: In this lab I will be interacting with Pfsense to Pfsense IPsec tunnel mode VPN. The VPN is setup between the 4 firewalls in the middle (Pfsense01, Pfsense02, Pfsense03, and Pfsense04). The tunnels are setup in Virtual Tunnel Interface (VTI) mode.
All the routers are running OSPF for routing over the VTI. Pfsense01 is the designated router with a router priority of 255 over the VTIs.
Pfsense01 is set as the default route for all the other routers (over the VPN). Basically Hop-in-Spoke VPN.
The OSPF network type is point-to-point.
